==English==

===Etymology===
A male [[given name]] of German origin meaning "Noble wolf". From Old High German adal = 'noble' and 'wolf, wulf' = 'wolf'.

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}
#{{given name|male|from Germanic|}} A male [[given name]].

